-- NODE 14: Agent Orange Environmental Legacy
(
  'Agent Orange Environmental Legacy — The Land Still Kills',
  'agent-orange-environmental-legacy',
  '20 million gallons of herbicides containing 366+ kg of dioxin sprayed over Vietnam (1961–1971). 3–4 million Vietnamese poisoned. Birth defects persist into third generation. Bien Hoa soil: 800x safe levels. U.S. promised $430M cleanup. Secretary Rubio halted funding March 2025.',
  E'# Agent Orange Environmental Legacy (1961–Present)\n\n## Summary\nBetween 1961-1971, the U.S. sprayed nearly 20 million gallons of herbicides — primarily Agent Orange containing 366+ kg of TCDD dioxin — over Vietnam. Estimated 3–4 million Vietnamese poisoned. Birth defects and cancers persist into third generation. At Bien Hoa airbase, dioxin levels measured at 800x allowable limits. March 2025: Secretary Rubio halted $430M committed cleanup funding.\n\n## The Evidence\n• Nearly 20 million gallons sprayed, 366+ kg TCDD dioxin 1961–1971 (Stellman, Nature, 2003)\n• 3–4 million Vietnamese exposed; birth defects persist into third generation (Vietnamese Red Cross; The Lancet)\n• Bien Hoa dioxin: 800x allowable limits — requiring removal of 40,000 dump trucks of soil\n• 1984: U.S. veterans settled with Dow/Monsanto for $180M — averaging $3,800 per veteran\n• Vietnamese civilians: received zero compensation from manufacturers\n• Nixon reportedly promised $3.25B reconstruction — payment never made\n• Da Nang cleanup (2018): $110M for single site; Bien Hoa far larger\n• March 2025: Sec. State Marco Rubio halted $430M committed cleanup funding\n\n## The Red Pill\nU.S. sprayed 20 million gallons of one of the most toxic substances on Earth over another country''s farmland. 3–4 million poisoned. Their grandchildren still born with defects. American veterans got $3,800 each. Vietnamese civilians got nothing. Companies that manufactured it never compensated a single Vietnamese victim. Soil at Bien Hoa is 800x over safety limit. Promised cleanup money halted 2025. The land still kills. Bill never paid.\n\n## Sources\nStellman, Jeanne Mager. "Agent Orange Usage Patterns." Nature, vol. 422, 2003.\nUSAID Vietnam. "Dioxin Contamination at Bien Hoa." 2020.\nReuters. "US Halts Agent Orange Cleanup Funding." March 2025.\nPalmer, Michael G. "Legacy of Agent Orange." The Lancet, vol. 369, 2007.',
  'Environmental & Health Studies',
  '1961-01-01',
  'verified',
  jsonb_build_object('category', 'Environmental & Corporate', 'pillar', 'Environmental & Corporate', 'years', '1961–Present', 'importance', 'GOLD', 'tags', ARRAY['Agent Orange', 'Vietnam War', 'dioxin', 'environmental contamination'], 'connection_web', ARRAY['Agent Orange', 'PFAS Forever Chemicals', 'Brazil Deforestation', 'Fukushima'])
),

-- NODE 15: Epstein-Intelligence Connection
(
  'The Epstein-Intelligence Connection',
  'epstein-intelligence-connection',
  'Jeffrey Epstein''s wealth has no verifiable origin. His partner''s father was buried with honors by six Israeli intelligence chiefs after stealing £460M. The prosecutor who gave Epstein a deal reportedly was told he "belonged to intelligence." JPMorgan processed $1.3B in suspicious transactions, reported almost none.',
  E'# The Epstein-Intelligence Connection (1980s–Present)\n\n## Summary\nWhen Epstein received a historically lenient 2008 plea deal — 13 months with daily work release — prosecutor Alexander Acosta reportedly told Trump transition he was told to "back off" because Epstein "belonged to intelligence." This claim traces to one anonymous source; Acosta denied it under oath. But the circumstantial architecture doesn''t require that quote to be damning.\n\n## The Evidence\n• Acosta reportedly told transition officials Epstein "belonged to intelligence" — sourced from one anonymous official; Acosta denied under oath (Daily Beast, 2019)\n• Robert Maxwell (Ghislaine''s father): documented MI6, Mossad, KGB asset; state funeral on Mount of Olives attended by 6 Israeli intelligence chiefs; had stolen £460M (Thomas & Dillon, 2002)\n• Les Wexner granted Epstein power of attorney; transferred $100M+ portfolio including Manhattan townhouse; Lolita Express registered to Wexner entity 1990–2001\n• JPMorgan maintained Epstein as client 15 years while failing to report $1.3B in suspicious transactions — roughly 300x amount actually flagged; settled $290M (USVI v. JPMorgan)\n• Deutsche Bank settled $75M; Bank of America settlement undisclosed\n• Ghislaine Maxwell convicted on 5 of 6 counts; 20 years (SDNY, June 2022)\n• Epstein''s wealth origin unexplained — Bear Stearns colleagues said he wasn''t standout trader; claimed hedge fund client list never verified; no Form 13F filings\n\n## The Red Pill\nEpstein''s wealth has no verifiable origin. His partner''s father was buried with honors by six Israeli intelligence chiefs after stealing £460M. Prosecutor who gave sweetheart deal reportedly was told he "belonged to intelligence." JPMorgan processed $1.3B suspicious transactions, reported almost none. Paid $290M — not to victims, but to settle negligence lawsuit. Maxwell serving 20 years. Client list sealed. 3M pages DOJ still withholding may explain what everyone suspects but nobody in power will say: this was never about one predator. It was an operation.\n\n## Sources\nThe Daily Beast. "Jeffrey Epstein: Acosta Told to Back Off." July 2019.\nThomas, Gordon & Martin Dillon. Robert Maxwell: Israel''s Superspy. Carroll & Graf, 2002.\n"USVI v. JPMorgan Chase: Settlement Agreement." SDNY, 2023.\n"United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell." SDNY, 2022.',
  'Court Records / Intelligence Report',
  '1980-01-01',
  'verified',
  jsonb_build_object('category', 'Child Safety & Trafficking', 'pillar', 'Child Safety & Trafficking', 'years', '1980s–Present', 'importance', 'PURE_GOLD', 'tags', ARRAY['Epstein', 'Maxwell', 'intelligence', 'JPMorgan', 'trafficking'], 'connection_web', ARRAY['Ghislaine Maxwell Trial', 'JPMorgan Settlement', 'Special Access Programs'])
);

